items.title: Did a Top Apple Executive Just Give Investors the Ultimate Reason to Dump the Stock?
items.description: An Apple executive recently testified at Google's antitrust case, and admitted that iPhones may not be needed in 10 years.  Artificial intelligence (AI) could result in a shift in users relying more on wearable devices.  Apple (NASDAQ: AAPL) has been one of the best stocks to own over the past five years on the stock market, rising more than 160% during that time frame.
